from the ones that care about teaching. It's not going to sink more money into the public school system because that is actually paid through your local government and your taxes. They would also be unable to dictate how the money was spent so that it would benefit the kids. It's also not going to make our government care less about grades and tests than it does about kids learning.   Stop blaming parents who care about their kid's education and would prefer to send them to private school! Would you get just as vocal about the parents who home school rather than send their kids to public school? "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="910" language="en" documentId="3256" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="Celtic_Pasta" date="Aug 29, 2013 7:30PM" docType="artcomment" origUrl="http://living.msn.com/family-parenting/the-family-room-blog-post?post=ab228ffc-1e99-4b37-a7b8-0b6a4c3fb240" topic="public-private-schools" thumbsUp="13" thumbsDown="0" origId="3256" notes="" title="Is it wrong to send kids to private school?"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="910"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39"/></xmi:XMI>